==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inclasp
<hw>In*clasp"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>clasp</ets>. Cf. <er>Enclasp</er>.]</ety>
<def>To clasp within; to hold fast to; to embrace or encircle.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>enclasp</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flattering ivy who did ever see⟦br⟧
<qex>Inclasp</qex> the huge trunk of an aged tree.</q> <rj><qau>F.
Beaumont.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inclaudent</ent>⟦br⟧
